                <h2 class="section-title">How to Pass the LM3 MCQ Exam – Exam Technique</h2>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <h3>Common LM3 Exam Traps</h3>
                    <p>1. Confusing managing agent and members' agent – the managing agent manages the syndicate; the members' agent advises the Name.</p>
                    <p>2. Assuming all FCA-authorised brokers can access Lloyd's – only Lloyd's-accredited firms have direct access.</p>
                    <p>3. Confusing FAL with the Central Fund – FAL is member-level capital (Layer 2); the Central Fund is drawn in Layer 3 only after FAL is exhausted.</p>
                    <p>4. Assuming binding authority coverholders negotiate terms – they bind within pre-agreed DUA parameters only.</p>
                    <p>5. The placing sequence: broker prepares slip → lead underwriter signs → following market subscribes → slip fully subscribed → LPSO processes → policy issued.</p>
                </div>

